&lt;P&gt;&lt;B&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ffffff&gt;8. What has been your worst of least favorite moment as being a Guide?&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ffffff&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ffffff&gt;Sometimez mes not find nobuddy to eet or play wif and dat can make eben a tuf troll have watery eyes. (Me always say dat its da bixie pollen tho...) &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ffffff&gt;&lt;B&gt;ooc&lt;/B&gt;: I think it's a toss up between being taken for granted (e.g. players who demand service or demand quests) and worrying that people don't see the value of the program or don't get fun out of it (e.g. the phrase "Oh yeah, just another dumb GM event" strikes an unpleasant chord in my heart. I suppose they are closely related. There are definitely times that I wish I could have infinite flexibility and somehow "magically" give every player exactly what they are looking for -- the challenge is figuring out "What do they want??" Sometimes, I don't think they know themselves... &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;B&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ffffff&gt;9. As a player have you every run into any Guides and events?&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ffffff&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ffffff&gt;Me runs into stuffs all da time. Momma sez I'm clum-see. &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ffffff&gt;&lt;B&gt;ooc&lt;/B&gt;: I was on one of the finalist teams for the Test of Tactics where our characters were transferred to one of the Zeks for server vs. server guild battles and I will always treasure my Golden Championship Ring. However, my absolutely most memorable moment was participating as a level 1 Halfling in the Halfling High Dive on my play server. Whatever guide thought to put us in a line, make us conga around the zone and then do the wave... was truly inspired. There is just nothing funnier than a train of 40 Halflings who are about to throw themselves off the edge of the world. Ridiculous funny!! &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;B&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ffffff&gt;10. What is your favorite thing about this Game?&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ffffff&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ffffff&gt;When me dies, me gets reincarnated and mes gets to go die again and again! Dats like magic!! &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ffffff&gt;&lt;B&gt;ooc&lt;/B&gt;: I think it's the feeling of adventure. I owe great thanks to a mystery player that I met 7 years ago -- I was a level 5 Shaman, and this bard offered to escort me across the Karanas. He stopped on the ascent to Highhold and said "Look up at this mural." I thought he was nuts, but we looked up at the mural on the wall and he said "I just can't believe that someone took the time and the energy to build in this much detail. It's a complete wonder everywhere you turn." and I just never looked at the game the same way. Each expansion holds something new and something exquisite and I still have great anticipation when I think about all there is left to explore. &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;B&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ffffff&gt;11. What do you plan to do in the future as a Guide? Any goals?&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ffffff&gt;I dunno, maybe me tries some new disguises. Me hears dat if yus find da right enchanter, yus can become a persistent dwarf. Me tinks dat sounds kinda fun! &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ffffff&gt;&lt;B&gt;ooc&lt;/B&gt;: I am definitely interested in learning more about all aspects of the guide program. I've really enjoyed recently taking on the role of Quest / Event Coordinator for my server and I hope that I can continue to participate in other ways as well -- learning about the Training program, writing some quests, or just branching out into new styles of role-play and player interaction. &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
